I can confirm that the following would represent a post with no author or comments:

```
{
    "relationships": {
        "author": {"data": null},
        "comments": {"data": []}
    }
}
```

Entire relationships should NOT be omitted to represent a lack of data, like this:

```
{
    "relationships": {}
}
```

Relationship objects may contain details, such as a `links` object with `self` and `related`. These links, or a `meta` object, could be present regardless of the current contents of `data`.

Note that the `data` member is only strictly required to fulfill the [full linkage](http://jsonapi.org/format/#document-compound-documents) requirement in compound documents. Besides that, `data` can be included as you wish, although I strongly recommend being consistent. In other words, don't leave off `data` just to indicate that relationships are empty.

