@elsigh unfortunately you're in the small percent that does things that way. If you cant trust my word (I've been doing Python, open source, and very active for a decade), you can simply look at the install numbers on the Python website. It's important to also note that pip != the python registry (PyPi).

We ship a standard Python app, that app versions dependencies (i.e. ua-parser >= 0.3.6), and it is not possible to ship a dependency that says "look for the version on GitHub). It's not supported by the Python build tools, and people that do this kind of stuff cant simply customize their installation for a minor dependency (ua-parser is one of 120+ third party dependencies we support).

If the python index won't be supported we'll simply fork ua-parser and version it ourselves, as the solutions proposed dont work for the greater python ecosystem.

